headline: Globe Life price target raised to $171 from $166 at Morgan Stanley
summary: Morgan Stanley raised the firm’s price target on Globe Life (GL) to $171 from $166 and keeps an Overweight rating on the shares. Following Q2 results, the firm is updating its price targets for stocks in the Life Insurance segment under its coverage, the analyst tells investors. Nearly half of the life insurers under its coverage beat expectations on a reported basis and most exceeded expectations on a core basis, the firm adds.
